what julia said about quality being more important than quantity is so spot on. i went to a tiny high school that on top of that, was overpacked, so it was easy to "know" everyone, but not everyone is your friend and i think as teenagers and maybe even younger adults, it's easy to want to have as many friends as possible because let's face it, life, and those years in particular, can get pretty lonely. but the phrase, "4 quarters are worth more than 100 pennies." is so true. loneliness and a need for friendship isn't quenched with a thousand friends. in fact, the more you have, the lonelier it gets, from my experience. you honestly could even just have one or two really really great friends and be totally satisfied.
